    "abstract": "1 Logical Entailment Given two statements x, y we write x ` y if x entails y. For example, if x = \u201cAll men are mortal\u201d y = \u201cSocrates is a man\u201d z = \u201cSocrates is mortal\u201d we can write (x \u2227 y) ` z. Entailment is a \u201ctruth broadcasting\u201d operation that allows the truth of the premises to flow to the conclusion. We also have the following simple theorem. Theorem 1 If x ` y then p(y|x) = 1. For example if x = \u201cAll swans are white\u201d y = \u201cAll swans in Austria are white\u201d",
